Demonstrates the per-station IEEE 802.11 data rate bar chart visualizer
(Ieee80211RateVisualizer).

A wired server sends UDP downlink traffic through an access point to three
wireless stations. The access point is configured to transmit to each station
at a different PHY data rate (6, 24 and 54 Mbps). The rate visualizer draws a
bar chart above the access point with one bar per station: bar height is
proportional to the rate, the rate is labelled on top of each bar, and the
rotated station names label the x axis.

Run in Qtenv and press Run to see the chart.
